description.narrative:
1.	Promote low-carbon development at local levels through development of pilot “Community Big Shift plans” (Community Energy Plans) with Christian Aid partners in at least 1 resettlement area and through partnership with the local government unit of Tacloban City on low carbon development and integration of renewable energy in their disaster risk reduction strategies;  
2.	Pilot  renewable energy solutions in women-led enterprise in Suluan island, Guian and in home-owners association/ peoples’ organization in 1 resettlement community in Tacloban City;
3.	Promote low-carbon development through influencing of public discussions and public funding programs to support climate-resilient and low-carbon development initiatives.
